Description. Head setae long, additional (a) and postpseudocular (pp) setae present, dorsal side with 2 + 2 modified setae, indicated of the arrows in
Fig. 1
. Rostrum very short, rounded (
Fig. 2
). Pseudoculus round, with distinct short lever, PR 14–19 (
Fig. 3
). Maxillary gland with large, densely granulated calyx; posterior filament short, with bilobed posterior dilation, CF 5.1–7.3 (
Fig. 4
). Maxillary palps short, dorsal sensillum shorter and thicker than lateral sensillum (
Fig. 5
). Labial palps well developed, with broad basal sensillum (
Fig. 6
). Labium with smooth inner margin.

